# Development Guidelines

## Code Style and Standards

### General Principles
- **Prefer terse answers**: Keep code concise and readable
- **If-guard style**: Structure conditional trees with early returns, avoiding deep nesting
- **Component-first**: Break down UI into reusable components
- **Type safety**: Use TypeScript for all components and utilities

### File Naming Conventions
- **Astro components**: PascalCase with `.astro` extension (e.g., `ProfileMode.astro`)
- **React components**: PascalCase with `.tsx` extension (e.g., `ThemeToggle.tsx`)
- **Pages**: kebab-case for routes (e.g., `about.astro`, `blog/[slug].astro`)
- **Utilities**: camelCase with `.ts` extension (e.g., `themeUtils.ts`)

### Component Structure
```astro
---
// Astro component frontmatter
interface Props {
  title: string;
  optional?: boolean;
}

const { title, optional = false } = Astro.props;
---

<div class="component-wrapper">
  <!-- Component content -->
</div>

<style>
  /* Minimal scoped styles only when necessary */
</style>
```

### Styling Guidelines
- **Tailwind first**: Use Tailwind CSS classes for styling
- **shadcn UI**: Leverage shadcn components for interactive elements
- **Minimal global CSS**: Keep [src/styles/global.css](mdc:src/styles/global.css) minimal
- **Responsive design**: Mobile-first approach with Tailwind breakpoints
- **Dark mode**: Use Tailwind's dark mode classes with theme provider

### Component Organization
- **UI components**: Place in `src/components/ui/` (shadcn components)
- **Layout components**: Place in `src/components/` (Header, Footer, etc.)
- **Page-specific components**: Co-locate with pages when appropriate

## Hugo PaperMod Reference Guidelines

### When Converting Components
1. **Study the original**: Always examine the Hugo template first
2. **Preserve functionality**: Maintain the same user experience
3. **Modernize implementation**: Use React/Astro patterns instead of Hugo templating
4. **Match styling**: Replicate the visual design using Tailwind

### Key Hugo Files to Reference
- [hugo-PaperMod/layouts/partials/index_profile.html](mdc:hugo-PaperMod/layouts/partials/index_profile.html) - Profile mode layout
